1. Environment setup
() Prerequisites
apt install build-essential cmake flex ninja-build

(a) Bison
We require Bison 3.1 or above which might not be in the repository, depending on the GNU/Linux distro used (see documentation for more info). Thus we compile Bison from sources.
apt purge bison
curl https://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/bison/bison-3.5.tar.xz --output bison-3.5.tar.xz
tar -xvf bison-3.5.tar.xz
cd bison-3.5
./configure
make
make install

(b) GCC
We require GCC v8 or above; if it is not the default compiler, we must set it as such.
apt install gcc-8 g++-8
export CC=gcc-8
export CXX=g++-8

(c) Python
We require a Python 3.8 environment:
apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv python3.8 python3.8-venv
python3.8 -m venv ~/.python3.8
. ~/.python3.8/bin/activate
pip install -U pip wheel
pip install -r requirements.txt 

2. Building
mkdir build && cd build
cmake -GNinja ..
ninja

3. Running
src/cpq ../tests/test.ou
src/cpq ../tests/test_imm.ou
src/cpq ../tests/test_casts.ou
src/cpq ../tests/test_expressions.ou
src/cpq ../tests/test_while.ou
src/cpq ../tests/test_switch.ou
src/cpq ../tests/test_error.ou
src/cpq ../tests/test_multiple_errors.ou
